// Hand-maintained: NOT generated by mmtorust.
//
// Rust port of `OMCompiler/Compiler/Util/SimulationResults.mo`, whose bodies
// are all `external "C"` wrappers over
// `OMCompiler/Compiler/runtime/SimulationResults.c` (a result-file reader for
// .mat-v4 / .plt / .csv with a process-global cache, `simresglob`) and
// `SimulationResultsCmp.c` / `SimulationResultsCmpTubes.c` (result
// comparison). mmtorust can only emit `todo!()` for `external "C"` bodies,
// so this module is hand-written and `SimulationResults` is listed in
// `HANDWRITTEN_TOP_PACKAGES` (mmtorust/src/codegen.rs) to skip its codegen.
//
// Current state: only [`close`] is implemented (the per-process reader cache
// does not exist yet, so releasing it is a no-op — but `simulate()` calls it
// unconditionally before each run and must not fail). The readers and
// comparison functions stay as explicit `todo!()`s until something exercises
// them; whoever implements them first needs a .mat-4 reader equivalent to
// `SimulationRuntime/c/util/read_matlab4.c`, plus the per-process cache that
// `close` must then clear.

